references: We analyzed Starlit‚Äôs efficiency with different SecureBoost configurations. The evaluation‚Äôs results are illustrated in Table 3. SecureBoost offers various options that can be employed to enhance efficiency in different settings. For instance, both direct sampling999This direct sampling approach is taken to reduce the training time. It works by randomly using only the stated fraction of the training set. and GOSS sampling offers a means to reduce network and memory overhead by decreasing the volume of data processed in each round of training.

As illustrated in Table 3, Starlit achieves its highest AUPRC level (i.e., 0.6520.6520.652) when the tree‚Äôs depth is set to 555. Remarkably, in this instance, Starlit‚Äôs AUPRC surpasses even the baseline setting (i.e., 0.6520.6520.652 versus 0.47150.47150.4715).
